                    <span>I bought this book despite it's bad reviews and I must say that I am sorry I did. This book is very poorly written. I got only to chapter 3 and the examples have led me to debug to get them to work. Example, chapter 3 asks you to connect to an Access database (OleDB) with a SQL Object! No, no. It also in the same chapter references a view in the PROVIDED Access database off the disk named OrderTotals thats not even there! 
<br />
<br />I would have given this 0 stars, but it was not an option.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">This is a very frustrating book for C# programmers. </div>
