                    <span>The book for me basically killed 3 birds with one stone. I am an experienced database application developer, but not in vb.net, c#, or ado.net. I did the exercises both in vb.net and c#. As for the program bugs, annoying, but having to debug some of the programs just helped me learn the language syntax. As for the ado.net, not confusing, but would have like to see more details in the concepts/topics the chapters were trying to explain. Over all, the book for me was nice fast-track into the technology, but limiting in details.</span>
                  
